HEADWORD: coccidiosis
<hw>coccidiosis</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>any of a group
of infectious diseases caused by protozoan parasites (coccidia) of the
order <ord>Coccidia</ord>, which infect the intestines of birds, dogs,
and other vertebrates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

